Script Plus: Clean up all side effects
script-plus.commands.scriptControl.execu: Script Plus: Execute Current Script (Using default configs)
script-plus.configs.node.packageManager: Specifies the package manager to install packages.
script-plus.configs.packages.dependencyS: Specifies how to determine the versions of dependencies when exporting a script.
script-plus.configs.packages.includePrer:
Whether to include pre-release version of packages in module search.
When set to true, the version list of large packages may be very long.
script-plus.configs.packages.installPosi:
Position to install packages.
When set to `local`, packages will be installed in extension global storage.
When set to `global`, packages will be installed in the pacakge manager's global folder.
script-plus.configs.script.transformer: Specifies the transformer to transform script code into CommonJS syntax.
script-plus.configs.startUp.autoCheck: Whether to check folder on activate.
script-plus.configs.startUp.autoScripts: The scripts to automatically run on startup.
script-plus.configs.startUp.checkExtensi: Whether to check extension dependencies (especially `esbuild`) on start up.
script-plus.configs.startUp.warnLocale: Whether to show locale warning on start up.
